flowRoot.flowPara: While there is no one person, country, or company responsible for climate change, the latest research and data can give us a pretty good idea of who and what contributes the most.
For starters, according to data put forth by scientists from Cambridge University, in 2010, a whopping 67.3% of emissions put forth were from the burning of fossil fuels.
